This paper is about generating adversarial texts, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves using machine learning algorithms to generate the adversarial texts, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The paper also involves using visual analytics to aid in the generation process, which falls under the subfield of machine learning (ML) and specifically, visual analytics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category. The paper also involves identifying and mitigating adversarial threats, which falls under the subfield of computer security (CR), making cs.CR another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves using word swapping to generate adversarial texts, which falls under the subfield of computer vision (CV), making cs.CV a less likely but still possible sub-category.
